[32m'Masked text for sample 4, segment 2373-2757: .\n\nWait, let me recheck my solution.\n\nTo determine whether the given answer is correct, we can use the relationship between the interior and exterior angles of a regular polygon.\n\n1. **Relationship between Interior and Exterior Angles:**\n   - The sum of the interior angle and the exterior angle of a polygon is always \\(180^\\circ\\).\n   - If the measure of an interior angle is \\(6.5\\) times the measure of an exterior angle, we can express this as:\n     \\[\n     \\text{Interior Angle} = 6.5 \\times \\text{Exterior Angle}\n     \\]\n\n2. **Sum of Exterior Angles:**\n   - The sum of all exterior angles of any polygon is \\(360^\\circ\\).\n   - If the polygon has \\(n\\) sides, each exterior angle is \\(\\frac{360^\\circ}{n}\\).\n\n3. **Equation Setup:**\n   - Let the exterior angle be \\(x\\).\n   - Then the interior angle is \\(6.5x\\).\n   - Since the interior and exterior angles are supplementary:\n     \\[\n     x + 6.5x = 180^\\circ\n     \\]\n     \\[\n     7.5x = 180^\\circ\n     \\]\n     \\[\n     x = \\frac{180^\\circ}{7.5} = 24^\\circ\n     \\]\n\n4. **Calculate Number of Sides:**\n   - Since each exterior angle is \\(24^\\circ\\), and the sum of all exterior angles is \\(360^\\circ\\):\n     \\[\n     n = \\frac{360^\\circ}{24^\\circ} = 15\n     \\]\n\nTherefore, the given answer of 15 sides is correct.<|im_end|>\n'[0m
